description: Uncertain; possibly from the English slang term chat (“louse”). The word predates the chadless punch, which therefore cannot be its origin, and a derivation from Scots chad (“river gravel”) stated in some dictionaries is now thought to be nothing more than guesswork.

nouns.description: chad (countable and uncountable, plural chad or chads)

entries.meaning: (uncountable) Small pieces of paper punched out from the edges of continuous stationery, or from ballot papers, paper tape, punched cards, etc.
(countable) One of these pieces of paper.

description: From ch- +‎ had, from ich + had.

entries.meaning: (Internet slang, seduction community, incel slang) Alternative spelling of Chad (“alpha-male; a virile man”)
